parameters: MWP_INVALID
\N<Waiter>I'm sorry, but we are currently fully booked...
\CE[79]\N<Rain>Huh? It looks like there are empty seats though...

\N<Waiter>Yes, that's correct... Currently, we have reached
the limit of the number of people we can serve
with food...

\N<Waiter>Sigh... The chef is too obsessed with creating new
dishes, so the kitchen isn't functioning properly.
If things continue like this, this restaurant will
eventually go out of business...
"sf_sweat"
\CE[84]\N<Rain>That's a problem... Can't we discuss it?

\N<Waiter>Of course, I conveyed this situation and tried to
talk about it, but he didn't listen... For the
restaurant, what the chef says is absolute...

\N<Waiter>Sigh... Maybe if we could at least get the
ingredients he's looking for, he might be willing
to listen a little...

\N<Waiter>We can't just close the restaurant, and besides,
we don't have that kind of money...
"empty"

\CE[84]\N<Rain>Alright, I understand. As a knight, I can't just
ignore someone in need. Let me try talking to him.
\N<Waiter>Oh, you're a knight! That's a relief!

\N<Waiter>You can enter the kitchen through the entrance
behind me. Please take care!
A
